# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Daksh SCRA — Environment Configuration Template
#
# Copy this file to .env and uncomment / set the values for your environment.
# Docker Compose reads .env automatically on startup.
#
# DO NOT commit .env to version control — it contains paths specific to your
# machine. Only .env.example belongs in the repository.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Web UI port (default: 8080)
DAKSH_PORT=8080

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Volume mounts — set these to host paths that should be accessible inside
# the container. See platform-specific examples below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Primary scan target: the host directory mounted to /scan-targets inside
# the container. Point this at the root of the codebase you want to scan.
#
# Windows / WSL:   DAKSH_SCAN_ROOT=/mnt/c
# Linux:           DAKSH_SCAN_ROOT=/home
# macOS:           DAKSH_SCAN_ROOT=/Users
#DAKSH_SCAN_ROOT=

# Generic host mount: exposed as /host and /mnt inside the container.
# Use this to make a broad section of your filesystem browsable.
#
# Windows / WSL:   DAKSH_HOST_MOUNT=/mnt
# Linux:           DAKSH_HOST_MOUNT=/
# macOS:           DAKSH_HOST_MOUNT=/
#DAKSH_HOST_MOUNT=

# Windows drive mounts (WSL only).
# These expose individual drives as /host/c and /host/d inside the container.
# Leave unset or remove these lines if you are not on Windows/WSL.
#
# DAKSH_HOST_C=/mnt/c
# DAKSH_HOST_D=/mnt/d
#DAKSH_HOST_C=
#DAKSH_HOST_D=

# Docker Desktop host bridge (Windows / macOS with Docker Desktop).
# The default value is the standard Docker Desktop path — change only if
# your Docker Desktop uses a custom mount point.
DAKSH_DESKTOP_MOUNT=/run/desktop/mnt/host

# Optional: mount a specific source directory directly.
# Useful when you want to restrict browsing to one project folder.
# Leave unset to rely on DAKSH_SCAN_ROOT instead.
#
# Example:  DAKSH_HOST_SOURCE=/home/user/projects
#DAKSH_HOST_SOURCE=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Directory browser roots
#
# Comma-separated list of paths the Web UI directory browser is allowed to
# show. Only directories under these roots are browsable. The server validates
# every request against this list and returns 403 for anything outside it.
#
# The default (no value set) auto-detects suitable roots for the current OS:
#   Linux / WSL / Docker: /, /mnt, /home, /srv, /scan-targets, /host
#   macOS:                /, /Users, /Volumes
#   Windows:              C:\, D:\, and any other lettered drives that exist
#
# Override examples:
#   DAKSH_BROWSE_ROOTS=/scan-targets,/host,/mnt
#   DAKSH_BROWSE_ROOTS=/scan-targets,/host/c,/host/d,/run/desktop/mnt/host
#DAKSH_BROWSE_ROOTS=
